          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Small Business and Community Investments Expansion Act of 2015</b></p> <p> Amends the Federal Home Loan Bank Act to authorize Federal Home Loan Banks to make long-term secured advances to their members to provide funds to community development financial institutions.</p> <p>Requires a Bank, at the time of origination or renewal of a loan or advance, to obtain and maintain a security interest in collateral eligible pursuant to any secured loan for any community development financial institution. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-03-13T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
